Example of using CreDating

Xavier Didelot

2017-11-03

Initialisation

library(CreDating)
library(ape)
set.seed(0)

Data

We start by generating a random timed tree with 20 leaves and root in 2000:

phy <- simdatedtree(nsam = 20, dateroot = 2000)
plot(phy)
axisPhylo(backward = F)

We can extract the sampling dates as follows:

dates = leafDates(phy)

On each branch we observe a number of substitutions which is distributed \(\mathrm{Gamma}(rl,1)\) where \(l\) is the branch length and \(r\) is the substitution rate specific to this branch, which has mean 10 substitutions per year. We can simulate an observed phylogenetic tree and perform a root-to-tip analysis as follows:

obsphy=simobsphy(phy, rate=10,model='relaxedgamma',ratevar = 100)
res=roottotip(obsphy,dates,predInt='gamma',showTree=T)

##Unknown root

Lets say we dont know where the root is, we might consider as a guess that it is at

the midpoint:

{r} #obsphy=phangorn::midpoint(obsphy) #res=roottotip(obsphy, dates, predInt = 'gamma', showTree = T) #

Analysis

We run CreDating as follows:

res=credate(obsphy,dates,nbIts = 10000,model='relaxedgamma',findRoot = 0,showProgress=F,initRate=10,initRatevar = 100,updateRatevar = T)
plot(res)

Plot with credibility bars:

plot(res,'treeCI')

We can see what the MCMC traces look like:

plot(res,'trace')

Lets see where the root is likely to be:
